Purified human heart cTnI (Calbiochem, LaJolla, CA, USA) was dissolved in urea/Tris buffer according to the manufacturer’s instructions. Monoclonal mouse anti-cTnI clone 19C7 (directed against amino acid sequence 40–50) and monoclonal mouse anti-cTnI clone 6F9 (directed against amino acid sequence 189-195) were purchased from HyTest (Turku, Finland). The enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) was based on the sandwich principle as described previously [13]. The percentage cTnI released from each culture equalled \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
